1
00:00:12,541 --> 00:00:13,666
[HAJIME]
Okay.

2
00:00:13,750 --> 00:00:15,833
This one's done,
wanna take a look?

3
00:00:15,916 --> 00:00:19,125
[KOKONOTSU]
Yeah, sure. That was fast.

4
00:00:19,208 --> 00:00:21,500
Whoa! You're good!

5
00:00:21,583 --> 00:00:25,166
Aw. Thanks. Just let me know
if you want any changes.

6
00:00:25,250 --> 00:00:28,083
No. In fact, it's great!

7
00:00:28,166 --> 00:00:32,041
[SAYA] Sorry for the wait!
I made some coffee.

8
00:00:32,125 --> 00:00:34,916
I used the coffee maker from
our café, so it's legit.

9
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:36,958
Thanks so much, Saya.

10
00:00:37,041 --> 00:00:37,916
I brought you some as well.

11
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:38,916
Coconuts.

12
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:40,791
[OTHERS]
Hm?

13
00:00:40,875 --> 00:00:44,791
A liquid slime joined my party.

14
00:00:44,875 --> 00:00:45,750
Hell yeah!

15
00:00:45,833 --> 00:00:48,541
Oh. Cool, that's great news.

16
00:00:48,625 --> 00:00:52,041
Question. What time do you
need this done by again?

17
00:00:52,125 --> 00:00:55,416
[KOKONOTSU] Let's see,
factoring in the travel time,

18
00:00:55,500 --> 00:00:56,958
nine in the morning.

19
00:00:57,041 --> 00:00:58,000
[HAJIME]
Got it!

20
00:00:58,083 --> 00:01:00,583
There.

21
00:01:00,666 --> 00:01:02,458
Okay. This page is ready.

22
00:01:02,541 --> 00:01:03,666
Thanks a lot.

23
00:01:03,750 --> 00:01:05,583
Man, the metal slime
I was fighting ran away!

24
00:01:05,666 --> 00:01:06,875
[SAYA]
Stop being so damn loud

25
00:01:06,958 --> 00:01:09,208
and go start on another
pot of coffee, loser!

26
00:01:09,291 --> 00:01:10,458
[TO]
Ow!

27
00:01:14,083 --> 00:01:17,583
[TO snoring]

28
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:24,416
[SAYA]
Here.

29
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:25,625
It's nice and fresh.

30
00:01:25,708 --> 00:01:27,708
Thanks, Saya.

31
00:01:27,791 --> 00:01:28,583
Hot!

32
00:01:28,666 --> 00:01:31,291
Well, duh! I did just make it.

33
00:01:46,625 --> 00:01:47,416
[BOYS laughing]

34
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:49,125
Hey! Hurry up, guys!

35
00:01:49,208 --> 00:01:50,625
[BOY B]
Wait for us!

36
00:01:58,708 --> 00:02:00,666
It's finally done.

37
00:02:00,750 --> 00:02:05,000
We're a pretty awesome
team. Oh, yeah!

38
00:02:05,083 --> 00:02:07,375
Well, I'm happy you finished.

39
00:02:07,458 --> 00:02:10,000
Way to go! All right,
so what's next?

40
00:02:11,333 --> 00:02:13,000
Coconuts?

41
00:02:13,083 --> 00:02:14,125
Coconuts!

42
00:02:14,208 --> 00:02:15,750
[HAJIME]
Manager?

43
00:02:17,083 --> 00:02:19,375
[KOKONOTSU snores]

44
00:02:19,458 --> 00:02:21,666
[SAYA]
At least he's not dead.

45
00:02:24,708 --> 00:02:29,666
♪


46
00:03:54,625 --> 00:03:56,958
[HAJIME] Hurry up,
or you're gonna be late!

47
00:03:58,291 --> 00:04:00,333
Yeah, 'kay!

48
00:04:12,166 --> 00:04:13,916
[CONDUCTOR A]
The next stop is Hata.

49
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:17,125
I repeat, the next stop is Hata.

50
00:04:18,833 --> 00:04:21,375
Uh, let's see.

51
00:04:21,458 --> 00:04:24,041
According to this, the
on-site manga review event

52
00:04:24,125 --> 00:04:26,125
should be in that bookstore.

53
00:04:26,208 --> 00:04:29,291
All right, it's time
to do this thing.

54
00:04:34,666 --> 00:04:36,666
[MAN A]
Man, this is nerve-wracking.

55
00:04:36,750 --> 00:04:39,750
The guy reviewing us is an
actual professional, right?

56
00:04:39,833 --> 00:04:41,958
Yeah, I've participated before,

57
00:04:42,041 --> 00:04:44,458
but it never gets any
easier, you know?

58
00:04:45,416 --> 00:04:46,583
[bell rings]

59
00:04:48,458 --> 00:04:49,666
[SAYA]
Miss Hajime!

60
00:04:49,750 --> 00:04:52,791
Uh-huh, that's me.

61
00:04:52,875 --> 00:04:54,750
It's freezing out there.

62
00:04:54,833 --> 00:04:57,166
Wow, your café is
like super cute.

63
00:04:57,250 --> 00:04:59,250
Uh, why'd I come here?

64
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:02,166
Oh, yeah, thanks for your
help yesterday-slash-today.

65
00:05:02,250 --> 00:05:06,000
Ah, gee. I mean, all I
did was make some coffee.

66
00:05:06,083 --> 00:05:08,458
And my useless brother
literally did nothing.

67
00:05:08,541 --> 00:05:10,750
Uh, hey now, that's not true.

68
00:05:10,833 --> 00:05:14,083
I cleared four entire games
yesterday-slash-today!

69
00:05:14,166 --> 00:05:16,416
In what world is
that helpful, idiot?

70
00:05:16,500 --> 00:05:19,000
Actually, your game did provide
some background noise,

71
00:05:19,083 --> 00:05:20,083
which kind of helped.

72
00:05:20,166 --> 00:05:21,708
It's not noise.

73
00:05:21,791 --> 00:05:25,958
[SAYA] Anyway, I wonder how the
review is going for Coconuts.

74
00:05:26,041 --> 00:05:29,000
Just thinking about him
out there makes me nervous.

75
00:05:29,083 --> 00:05:30,375
Here's your coffee.

76
00:05:30,458 --> 00:05:33,458
Seriously, she's been goin'
on like this all day.

77
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:34,791
So what?

78
00:05:34,875 --> 00:05:37,875
Coconuts might become a
professional manga artist!

79
00:05:37,958 --> 00:05:39,375
I think it's exciting.

80
00:05:39,458 --> 00:05:41,000
[HAJIME chuckles]

81
00:05:41,083 --> 00:05:44,000
This smells great.

82
00:05:44,083 --> 00:05:47,541
Oh, hey, maybe we should throw
a party for him to celebrate!

83
00:05:47,625 --> 00:05:49,208
Calm down, Saya.

84
00:05:49,291 --> 00:05:51,833
If anything, it'd be more
like a wrap-party.

85
00:05:51,916 --> 00:05:53,250
Yeah.

86
00:05:53,333 --> 00:05:54,791
Still though,

87
00:05:54,875 --> 00:05:58,208
we should probably hold off
on any party plans for today.

88
00:05:58,291 --> 00:06:01,083
[KOKONOTSU]
Holy crap, I am so nervous!

89
00:06:01,166 --> 00:06:02,166
[door opens]

90
00:06:02,250 --> 00:06:04,000
[WOMAN A]
Mister Kokonotsu Shikada?

91
00:06:04,083 --> 00:06:04,750
You're next.

92
00:06:04,833 --> 00:06:05,875
[KOKONOTSU]
Here!

93
00:06:07,041 --> 00:06:09,083
Really? Why's that?

94
00:06:09,166 --> 00:06:10,416
[HAJIME]
Because...

95
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:13,625
I get the feeling he may
not be up to celebrating.

96
00:06:18,541 --> 00:06:19,208
[EDITOR A]
You--

97
00:06:19,291 --> 00:06:21,083
Uh, yes?

98
00:06:21,166 --> 00:06:22,666
You are amazing!

99
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:25,041
At your level, you could
probably start right away.

100
00:06:25,125 --> 00:06:28,000
Yeah! You might even
win best new manga!

101
00:06:28,083 --> 00:06:30,708
Uh, say what?

102
00:06:30,791 --> 00:06:32,916
[ANNOUNCER A] The manga <i>Spin</i> ,
by Kokonotsu Shikada,

103
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,166
is a sensation.

104
00:06:34,250 --> 00:06:36,833
Bookstores can't seem
to keep them in stock.

105
00:06:36,916 --> 00:06:38,583
[WOMAN B]
<i>Spin</i> is my favorite!

106
00:06:38,666 --> 00:06:41,208
[WOMAN C]
Kokonotsu is the coolest!

107
00:06:41,291 --> 00:06:44,333
[ANNOUNCER B] The Japan Best
New Manga Award goes to--

108
00:06:44,416 --> 00:06:47,000
<i>Spin</i> , by Kokonotsu Shikada!

109
00:06:47,083 --> 00:06:49,250
Congratulations!

110
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:52,166
Uh. Thank you, it's an honor.

111
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:56,750
Ho...

112
00:07:01,708 --> 00:07:03,541
[KOKONOTSU]
Uh.

113
00:07:03,625 --> 00:07:05,625
So, how long did this take?

114
00:07:05,708 --> 00:07:08,041
Well, uh...

115
00:07:08,125 --> 00:07:10,416
[KOKONOTSU] I started on
the story three months ago,

116
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:12,875
but the actual drawing
time was only around

117
00:07:12,958 --> 00:07:16,250
two to three weeks,
give or take.

118
00:07:16,333 --> 00:07:17,625
Two weeks, maybe?

119
00:07:17,708 --> 00:07:20,708
Uh, well, yes, sir.
That's right.

120
00:07:20,791 --> 00:07:23,791
Ah. Okay, that's good.

121
00:07:23,875 --> 00:07:25,625
[KOKONOTSU]
Yeah. I guess.

122
00:07:27,375 --> 00:07:29,791
[KOKONOTSU]
Of course, I had help.

123
00:07:30,791 --> 00:07:33,791
Is there a reason you couldn't
spend more time on it?

124
00:07:33,875 --> 00:07:35,666
[gasps]

125
00:07:35,750 --> 00:07:37,000
[KOKONOTSU]
Um.

126
00:07:37,083 --> 00:07:39,916
Look, I wish I could go
over it more page by page.

127
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:43,833
But since there are more people
to review, I'll sum it up.

128
00:07:43,916 --> 00:07:46,958
You haven't learned how
to budget your time yet.

129
00:07:47,041 --> 00:07:50,416
Perhaps you're having
a hard time focusing?

130
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:53,083
Although you're clearly aware
of your artistic strengths,

131
00:07:53,166 --> 00:07:54,916
I think it's also clear
that you're avoiding

132
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,166
your weak points.

133
00:07:56,250 --> 00:07:59,166
Stop making excuses.

134
00:07:59,250 --> 00:08:02,000
If I had to guess, I'd say you
probably did most of this work

135
00:08:02,083 --> 00:08:03,583
over the past few days.

136
00:08:03,666 --> 00:08:05,291
I will give you credit
for at least finishing it

137
00:08:05,375 --> 00:08:07,958
by the deadline, though.

138
00:08:08,041 --> 00:08:12,708
But look on the bright side.
You have years to improve.

139
00:08:16,666 --> 00:08:18,458
[KOKONOTSU]
It ended in five minutes.

140
00:08:18,541 --> 00:08:20,583
It took me three
hours to get here,

141
00:08:20,666 --> 00:08:23,875
and the whole review ended
in five friggin' minutes.

142
00:08:23,958 --> 00:08:25,833
I can focus just fine.

143
00:08:25,916 --> 00:08:28,875
And what excuses?
What did he mean?

144
00:08:28,958 --> 00:08:31,916
I was just busy
running the shop.

145
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:35,833
If I don't look after
it... If I don't...

146
00:08:38,125 --> 00:08:40,791
Wait, why am I the
manager again?

147
00:08:52,625 --> 00:08:54,333
[HAJIME]
Um, I'm sorry.

148
00:08:54,416 --> 00:08:56,666
I didn't mean to bring
down the mood earlier.

149
00:08:56,750 --> 00:08:58,083
Hey, it's cool.

150
00:08:58,166 --> 00:09:01,250
Besides, I think I was the
one who got carried away.

151
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:02,500
[HAJIME]
Well, hopefully I'm wrong

152
00:09:02,583 --> 00:09:04,875
and he'll get good news instead.

153
00:09:04,958 --> 00:09:06,750
Oh, look.

154
00:09:06,833 --> 00:09:08,750
It's starting to snow.

155
00:09:10,125 --> 00:09:11,250
[ANNOUNCER A]
Due to the inclement weather,

156
00:09:11,333 --> 00:09:12,458
some of the train routes

157
00:09:12,541 --> 00:09:15,208
may be experiencing
cancellations or delays.

158
00:09:15,291 --> 00:09:16,958
At this time, we are
unsure when the trains

159
00:09:17,041 --> 00:09:19,000
will resume their
regular schedule.

160
00:09:19,083 --> 00:09:21,583
We apologize for
the inconvenience.

161
00:09:21,666 --> 00:09:23,583
[KOKONOTSU]
Just my luck.

162
00:09:35,750 --> 00:09:39,375
[KOKONOTSU] I wonder when the
trains will start running again.

163
00:09:39,458 --> 00:09:41,791
It's probably better
that they aren't.

164
00:09:41,875 --> 00:09:45,708
I'm not sure I could face
everyone back home anyway.

165
00:09:45,791 --> 00:09:50,208
Saya, To, and Hajime...
I let them all down.

166
00:10:00,916 --> 00:10:02,791
[KOKONOTSU]
Maybe I should give up.

167
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:06,833
[door opens]

168
00:10:11,166 --> 00:10:11,916
[HOTARU]
Oh.

169
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,125
[KOKONOTSU gasps]

170
00:10:14,666 --> 00:10:16,750
This is a nice surprise.

171
00:10:24,875 --> 00:10:25,958
[gasps]

172
00:10:31,250 --> 00:10:33,875
What brings you out
here, Kokonotsu?

173
00:10:39,541 --> 00:10:43,791
Uh, hello there, Hotaru.

174
00:10:43,875 --> 00:10:46,416
[HOTARU]
It's been a while, hasn't it?

175
00:10:48,458 --> 00:10:53,416
♪


176
00:12:19,083 --> 00:12:19,958
[HOTARU]
Next time:

177
00:12:20,041 --> 00:12:22,333
"I'm back, Welcome Back, and..."

178
00:12:22,416 --> 00:12:24,916
Did you miss me, Kokonotsu?

